<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Waltz texture throughout: LH bass note on beat 1, chord on beats 2-3 (oom-pah-pah).
- RH fills out the texture above with 2-note or occasionally 3-note chords.
- Phrase 1 (mm. 2–5): Sparse I–IV progression; LH waltz bass establishes F/Bb/C.
- Phrase 2 (mm. 6–9): C major phrase gives harmonic variety. RH arpeggiated V in m.7.
- Phrase 3 (mm. 10–13): Richer version of phrase 1 — LH adds A3 upper note for fuller IV.
- Phrase 4 (mm. 14–17): Climax with Gm→C suspension in m.14 and ii–V–I close.
  m.14 uses sus4 suspension (G–C RH, resolves G–E) over V pedal.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- RH tenor line (lower voice): C5→A4→F4 stepwise descent across mm. 2–3.
- LH "thumb" walk: F→C→C / G→C→G / Bb→F→D / F→C→A — each change is a P4/P5 leap.
- m.16 ii–V pivot: G2-D3 (Gm) → Bb2 passing → C2-G2-E3 (V) — clean diatonic bass walk.
- No parallel 5ths between RH and LH; contrary motion at all main cadences.

TEXTURE ARC:
- mm. 1–5: Minimal — sparse pickup, 2-note RH waltz, 2-note LH bass
- mm. 6–9: Same texture but C major color opens harmonic space
- mm. 10–13: Denser — 3-note RH, 3-note LH on beat 2, warmer
- mm. 14–17: Suspension (m.14) → flowing resolution → full I close
-->
